elements._description:
You are in a dimly lit room.
You see a sign 
"Welcome to Jorm. use the "look"
To look around a room.

Type "go [exit name]" to proceed"
Is this what they call a seemless tutorial?

Again, welcome to JORM! This is the start of your adventure.
To the north is Pernion.
To the east is Ellenia.
To the south is Henesys.
And to the west is Kerning City.

You find yourself in the dimly lit streets of Kerning City.
A sprawling urban jungle. Neon signs flicker and hum.
Shadows dance along the graffiti covered walls of grimy brick buildings.
You find yourself at the base of the mountain, in the city of Perion. Where warriors come to climb the mountain to train and hone their skills.
You find yourself in the nice city of Henesys with a pleasant view of the the plains accompanied with a nice breeze.
You find yourself in the dense forest of Ellenia, a secluded city where the forest hums with life and magic.
The backstreets of Kerning city where anything can happen. But what is that smell... the sewers?
The backstreets of Kerning city where anything can happen

The night sky stretches endlessly above, you can see the city in the distance.
In the vertical distance...
The night sky stretches endlessly above, you can see the city in the distance.

A chaotic maze of half finished steel scaffolding.
Piles of concrete rubble and rusted bolts litters the floor.
Wooden beams are used to close the gaping holes between the floors.

Piles of discarded machinery and rusted barrels line the road.
The hum of distant power tools and the occasional clang of metal echo faintly.
A large skeletal framework of a construction site is here.

Its too dark to see anything in here.
You hear a paper rustle on the ground.
Pick it up with "get [item]".
then read whats on it with "identify [item]".

In the darkness you hear something hiss!
Use "fight" to fight all enemies in the room.

To attack an enemy type 
"use [skill] on [target]"

You can view your skills with "skills"

Example: "use swing on [enemy]"

If you fought your way in here, congratulations!

You might have even leveled up!
use "stats" to see your current exp.
If its above the required exp threshold.
you can level up!

Use "level [stat]" to level up a stat once.
You can level up "grit" "flow" "mind" or "soul".

You will also get practice points when you level up.
Use "practice" to view all skills you can learn.

"practice [skill name] [practice points]" 
To spend x amount of practice points on that skill.

To read about a skill.
Type "skill [skill name]" to get a better understanding of what it does

You are nearing the end now.

The last thing you need to know about is the "help" command

"help" by itself lists all commands in game.
"help [command]" displays information about that command.
try it! 

"help look"


And when you are ready, proceed.
